(7) A person shall not be appointed as a member of the Agency if the person— (a) is an undischarged bankrupt; (b) has been convicted of an offence involving fraud or dishonesty; or (c) has been convicted of an offence under any other written law and sentenced to a term of imprisonment of not less than six months, without the option of a fine.
